{"lemma":"أُرْفَةٌ","slug":"أُرْفَةٌ","root":"#.ر.ف","root_slug":"_-ر-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ر-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n601","n16243"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%92%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n601","headword_ar":"اُرْفَةٌ","root":"Arf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A limit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boundary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making a separation"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between two pieces of land;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T, S, Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the limits,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boundaries, between two pieces of land:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a separation between houses and estates:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a dam between two pieces of land sown or for sowing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, M:) Yaakoob asserts that its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a substitute for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"v","text_ar":"ث"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^urovapN","text_ar":"اُرْثَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is, however, less com-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":50},{"kind":"text","text":"mon]: (M:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^urafN","text_ar":"اُرَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, &c.,) signifying, accord. to Lh, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uravN","text_ar":"اُرَثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limits,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boundaries, between two pieces of land"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]; (T;) and it is said in a trad., that these cut off"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ufoEap","text_ar":"الشُّفْعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the right of preemption]; (T, S, Mgh;) meaning, in the language of the people of El- Hijáz,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"signs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"marks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limits,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boundaries."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) Th relates that an Arab woman said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEala","text_ar":"جَعَلَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealay~a zawojiY A^urofapF laA A^ajuwzuhaA","text_ar":"عَلَيَّ زَوْجِى اُرْفَةً لَا اَجُوزُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My husband set me a sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beyond which I should not pass."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^urofapu A^ajalK","text_ar":"اُرْفَةُ اَجَلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An extreme limit of a period of existence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, from a trad.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A knot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K.)"}],"source_refs":["As","T","S","M","Mgh","Msb","K","Th"]},{"entry_id":"n16243","headword_ar":"ارفه","root":"rfh","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He found,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"experienced, rest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he remained, stayed, dwelt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode, and found,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"experienced, rest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinodinaA","text_ar":"عِنْدِنَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at our abode;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rf~h","text_ar":"رفّه","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarofiyhN","text_ar":"تَرْفِيهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAar, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astrfh","text_ar":"استرفه","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He kept continually,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constantly, to the eating of dainty food,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"indulged himself largely in eating and drinking:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this is said to be meant in a trad. in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_irofaAh","text_ar":"الاـِرْفَاه"},{"kind":"text","text":"is forbidden; because it is one of the practices of the foreigners and of worldly people. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He anointed himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and combed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anointed and combed, his hair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every day:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K:) and this also is said to be meant in the trad. above mentioned: (JK, S, TA:) or by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlArfAh","text_ar":"الارفاه"},{"kind":"text","text":"in that trad. is meant ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the indulging in"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ease and plenty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Arfhu AlmaAlu","text_ar":"ارفهُ المَالُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cattle remained near to the water"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the water-ing-trough"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tank, pasturing there upon the plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trees, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArfhwA","text_ar":"ارفهوا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Their camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their cattle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came to the water to drink"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every day,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when they would."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arofahahumo","text_ar":"اَرْفَهَهُمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(God)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made them to have an easy, a pleasant, a soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a delicate, and a plentiful, life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raf~ahahumo","text_ar":"رَفَّهَهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarofiyhN","text_ar":"تَرْفِيهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arofahotuhu","text_ar":"اَرْفَهْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raf~ahotuhu","text_ar":"رَفَّهْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made him to find,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"experience,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enjoy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 1,)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an easy, a pleasant, a soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a delicate, life, with ampleness of the means of subsistence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Arfh AlA_ibila","text_ar":"ارفه الاـِبِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rf~hhA","text_ar":"رفّهها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanohaA","text_ar":"عَنْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rf~h","text_ar":"رفّه","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. as above; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made the camels to come to the water to drink"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every day,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when they would."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","IAar","TA","JK","S","God"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}